#: ../../controller.rst:5 a2d04ff77c2645fe9d18ce381cdc44a3
msgid "Controller"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:7 b73f653016a74203b5c0a570a36c37bd
msgid ""
"The NethSecurity controller is an application that can run on `NethServer"
" 8 "
"<https://docs.nethserver.org/projects/ns8/en/latest/nethsecurity_controller.html>`_"
" (NS8). The controller allows remote control of multiple NethSecurity "
"installations, called units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:10 7a25c1d947b24b87a71055fdac93a6c2
msgid ""
"The firewall can operate independently without the need for the "
"controller. The controller is an optional component that provides "
"additional management and monitoring capabilities for the firewall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:13 d4a4e31124094feea2d445f111029334
msgid ""
"The controller creates a secure connection between the central server and"
" the units. Each firewall registers with the server using a client called"
" ns-plug. Once registered, the server generates a VPN configuration that "
"is sent back to the firewall. The VPN enables secure communication "
"between the controller and the unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:18 efd04ac5e60f40b491f89ebc48a63518
msgid "Key features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:20 c58b79f551a94e608d840bb89f2d1eff
msgid ""
"**Centralized Management**: Manage multiple firewalls from a single "
"server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:21 7e7ee2931f0743d48f7536998e621334
msgid ""
"**Secure Communication**: Establish a secure `OpenVPN "
"<https://openvpn.net/>`_ connection between the server and the firewalls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:22 f3dffacb9c9f42128cef1549107bb9ad
msgid ""
"**Easy Configuration**: Configure firewalls directly from the "
"controller's user interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:23 6ecd38e81c5b47d9acc634afbd0a682e
msgid ""
"**Monitoring and Logging**: Collect and analyze logs from the firewalls "
"inside `Loki <https://grafana.com/oss/loki/>`_ for troubleshooting and "
"monitoring purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:24 1182f62f0d4741bd92212e32b4ad54c0
msgid ""
"**Metrics Visualization**: Visualize metrics from the firewalls using the"
" built-in `Grafana <https://grafana.com/>`_ dashboard. Metrics are "
"collected using `Prometheus <https://prometheus.io/>`_ and `TimescaleDB "
"<https://www.timescale.com/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:26 61beb1a997234e869643f7b496a5f927
msgid ""
"**Web-based SSH**: Access the firewall command-line interface using a "
"web-based SSH client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:29 c6fda2004e54480395dd3e269fd6397f
msgid "Installation and configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:31 450f7abb481743c2b5aae46c41613f52
msgid ""
"The controller can be installed on a NethServer 8 system from the "
"Software Center. The module is named `NethSecurity Controller`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:33 61704a4cd6254d2aa39b8a76af5e9664
msgid ""
"After the installation, the controller must be configured. The "
"configuration can be done using the NethServer 8 web interface. The "
"following parameters need to be set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:36 fba467138e4e44f1a6f0446ac88685e5
msgid ""
"`Controller hostname`: The fully qualified domain name for the "
"controller, like: ``mycontroller.nethsecurity.org``. Ensure the hostname "
"is resolvable and reachable from the units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:38 efb8149a92374292ab4dd645ba81f2b5
msgid ""
"`Let's Encrypt certificate`: Enable or disable Let's Encrypt certificate "
"for the controller web interface. It's recommended to enable it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:39 faad01a5b5864f91959af1735e70f987
msgid ""
"`VPN network` and `VPN netmask`: The OpenVPN network and netmask. When "
"choosing the network, make sure it does not overlap with the existing "
"networks inside all the units that will be connected to the controller. "
"Use only class C networks like ``192.168.7.0`` with netmask "
"``255.255.255.0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:41 e4d647572b514ca2805026eb9f0fd13d
msgid ""
"`Administrator user`: The controller administrator user name. The "
"administrator user is the only user that can create and manage other "
"users inside the controller. The same user name is used to access the "
"Grafana interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:43 bd25ee7e6df049a1a25fc2ca36419465
msgid ""
"`Administrator password`: Choose a strong password for the administrator "
"user. Note that the default password is displayed only once, please store"
" it in a safe place. The same password is used to access the Grafana "
"interface. For security reasons, you should change the password after the"
" first login both for the controller and the Grafana interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:47 731b798bb9014856ad85fa3d22a6632e
msgid "The following parameters are optional:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:49 9ccbb861db2b4ba580ffb1c2a8b93b23
msgid ""
"`Controller name`: The name of the controller, used to create the VPN "
"certification authority. You can leave it unchanged unless you have a "
"specific requirement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:50 ba3b1a349bec4d209da4f8d5e244a9a4
msgid ""
"`Log retention`: The log retention period in days, default is 180 days. "
"It applies to the logs stored in Loki."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:51 b5305df2768e42c890c13501694d4480
msgid ""
"`Metrics retention`: The metrics retention period in days, default 15 "
"days. It applies to the metrics stored in Prometheus and Timescale."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:52 210c1515e1ba4ceabf7ceb718f47cbbd
msgid ""
"`MaxMind license key`: The controller can geolocate the IP addresses of "
"the connected VPN clients and attackers. A map with the location of the "
"clients and attackers will be displayed inside Grafana. The license key "
"is required to enable the feature and download the MaxMind GeoIP2 "
"database. To obtain a free license key, signup on the  `MaxMind website "
"<https://www.maxmind.com/en/geolite2/signup>`_, then access the `Manage "
"License Keys` page inside the account section. Generate a new license, "
"copy the license key and paste it in the field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:57 11e7e04bd6eb4ffcb9c165bef052311c
msgid ""
"After completing the configuration, the controller is ready to be used "
"and can be accessed using a web browser at the configured hostname, like "
"``https://mycontroller.nethsecurity.org``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:60 462e6e6daf5d4138823a0c0c270b7bb0
msgid "Users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:62 7b0f712c3a3c4b6493e10fdb808061a9
msgid "The controller has two types of users:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:64 1839ade34fbb4a178c399b8c0fd1ea62
msgid ""
"**Administrator**: The administrator user is the only one who can create "
"and manage users inside the controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:65 e19b53bee875441181ea001560ff9049
msgid "**User**: The user can manage the units and the firewall configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:67 bebdcc106f1a4bbab17693602a37ca11
msgid "The administrator is created during the controller configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:69 ce181a70743d44469b0b4d1ef1aaf6ee
msgid ""
"It is recommended to create a user for each person who needs access to "
"the controller. When creating a new user, the administrator must specify "
"the username, the user display name, and the user password. The username "
"is used to log in to the controller, while the display name is used to "
"identify the user in the controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:73 ed9eb307951a4398a7198a6fe79665a3
msgid "The administrator can also reset the user password and delete users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:75 72d37f3acb6d4fe5bff425f84602d234
msgid ""
"After logging in, each user can change their password and generate an SSH"
" key pair for accessing the unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:78 e2a8479f08f34924a95ff9316546ea0a
msgid "Two Factor Authentication (2FA)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:80 9eb88293c1004cea81f817eccd2bd9fd
msgid ""
"Each controller user can enable Two Factor Authentication (2FA) to "
"increase the security of the account. To enable 2FA, follow the same "
"steps documented inside the firewall web interface: :ref:`2fa-section`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:83 8e6cb80193304dbeaaac2acbc8db3bd9
msgid ""
"The administrator can see the 2FA status of each user inside the user "
"list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:86 6ca107974b9e4ce79b79aaaf41337647
msgid "Units"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:88 3db5f9f825794f5b9217fb681d9b4a5c
msgid ""
"All users can manage units. A unit is a firewall that is managed by the "
"controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:90 a02a8990b05b4dcc87d7ba410c6190da
msgid ""
"To connect a new unit to the controller, the user must click on the "
":guilabel:`Add unit` button from the controller web interface. When a new"
" unit is added, the controller performs the following actions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:93 2e0138831a50422c8650502dc1b406d6
msgid "creates a unique identifier for the unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:94 783cb3ab6d98438f9d1b0a2434ac859b
msgid "allocates an IP address inside the VPN network"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:95 d81021122b8c4718a6d507a81d173666
msgid "generates a VPN configuration including certificates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:96 5fb2222ec05143cbb317fb5fc28d9203
msgid "safely stores credentials required for accessing the remote firewall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:98 984e5ecd500447548a418e51f6397b65
msgid ""
"A join code will be generated and displayed on the screen. The join code "
"must be entered on the unit to establish the connection with the "
"controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:100 782169bf707442819d8831f8eea0391b
msgid ""
"Access the ``Controller`` page inside the unit web interface and enter "
"the join code in the ``Join code`` field. When joining the controller, "
"the unit will download the VPN configuration and establish a secure "
"connection with the controller. If the connection is successful, the unit"
" will be displayed in the controller web interface with the status "
"``Connected``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:104 99b9f3b603af4a119b9ba64723829341
msgid ""
"Please note that if the controller does not have a valid Let's Encrypt "
"certificate, you will need to disable the ``Verify TLS certificate`` "
"option in the unit configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:106 fabdc8b47af9416b9d9c8305670bc133
msgid ""
"When the unit is connected, the user can access the unit web interface by"
" clicking on the :guilabel:`Open unit` link without needing to enter the "
"unit credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:110 c2158a0c45574bef93e4e4e583ae64f9
msgid ""
"The unit user interface :ref:`must listen on port 9090 <change_ui_port-"
"section>` to allow the controller to access it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:113 63e9d3505047414e9e857b642965d3df
msgid "Remove a unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:114 b775c9c869d44317a59787ea1ffe5fdd
msgid ""
"Units can be disconnected from the controller by clicking on the "
":guilabel:`Remove unit` button from the controller web interface. When a "
"unit is disconnected, the controller will remove the unit configuration "
"and the VPN connection will be terminated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:117 20c592c3840c4338a17353b3a905b25e
msgid ""
"After removing the unit from the controller web interface, access the "
"unit web interface and click :guilabel:`Disconnect unit` on the "
"``Controller`` page: the unit will destroy the VPN configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:123 83c1491ed0574d1a8a8c3e2fd15a1e4c
msgid "Logs management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:125 31db770ccb88430687a88b3581d858e3
msgid ""
"When a unit is connected, rsyslog is reconfigured to send logs using the "
"syslog protocol (RFC 5424). It may take a few minutes before rsyslog "
"starts sending the data. The logs are labeled using the unit's hostname: "
"to ensure that the user interface links work properly, make sure that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:129 9a9397988c0f4f35befc6e2c0415f27d
msgid "the unit FQDN is unique within the cluster"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:130 35e887af722e428ca3683f58055c3525
msgid "the unit's name is the same as its hostname"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:132 c5b37ff3569144758402cdc9120e80bc
msgid ""
"Logs can be viewed by clicking on the :guilabel:`Open logs` link for each"
" unit. The logs are displayed in a specific Grafana dashboard that also "
"allows for searching and filtering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:136 02063baf92714026a7fcb3f7bdc45022
msgid "Logs retention period must be configured from the NS8 web interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:141 62c99ec0b14f4fff854710170648ddb3
msgid "Metrics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:143 7fa6485d1969462d95f5640f8288c8ff
msgid "Each unit exports two types of metrics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:145 0294eedeb3ed48e6a599b909da5a1b71
msgid ""
"system operating metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network): these metrics are "
"collected using `Netdata <https://www.netdata.cloud/>`_ and stored in "
"`Prometheus <https://prometheus.io/>`_. As soon as a unit is connected, "
"the controller starts scraping the metrics. These metrics are available "
"to everyone regardless of the subscription status."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:148 b8d785d824444a37aec7889c7c17dd58
msgid ""
"firewall metrics (traffic, security, VPN): these metrics are sent from "
"the unit to controller at fixed intervals. The controller stores them "
"inside a `Timescale <https://www.timescale.com/>`_ database. These "
"metrics are available only to users with a valid subscription."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:152 93fd450691bf439f982466708078d0c5
msgid ""
"All data collected and stored inside the controller is timestamped using "
"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This ensures consistency and accuracy "
"across different time zones, making it easier to correlate events and "
"analyze trends."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:155 617cde51ae664b4b8f3646bdc41217a8
msgid ""
"Users have the flexibility to view data in their local time zone by "
"adjusting the time settings in Grafana. To change the local time zone, "
"navigate to the Grafana preferences menu and select the desired time "
"zone. This adjustment can be applied to each dashboard individually, "
"allowing users to customize the time zone display based on their "
"preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:159 348e1b004865443eb8faa4ae425332da
msgid ""
"The metrics can be viewed within the Grafana dashboard. Users can access "
"the dashboard by clicking on the :guilabel:`Open metrics` link for each "
"unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:162 6dce218fdf8e48e3a49c3500d379448c
msgid ""
"By default, only the admin user can access the metrics dashboard. If you "
"want to allow other users to access the metrics dashboard, you can create"
" a new role and assign it to the user directly from the Grafana web "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:168 6ab9916d9c3c45388ff58aa17396205e
msgid "Grafana"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:170 2c6a2de386174869afd9eb292fc6b3e3
msgid ""
"Grafana is an open-source platform used for monitoring and visualizing "
"time-series data. It helps users create customizable dashboards with "
"graphs, charts, and tables to analyze system metrics, logs, and other "
"data from various sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:173 ae6dd5cd46f8478385f75ba16c1d3f8e
msgid ""
"The controller includes a pre-configured Grafana instance that is used to"
" visualize metrics and logs from the connected units. The Grafana "
"instance is accessible from the URL ``https://<controller-"
"fqdn>/grafana``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:176 cf9bb08293e84968b478926d2ae6e0d0
msgid ""
"By default, you can access it by using the default credentials set during"
" the controller configuration. Remember to change the default password "
"after the first login. Grafana also provides features for managing users,"
" teams, and permissions. It supports authentication via various methods "
"including username/password, OAuth, LDAP, and more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:181 3178d8ffbd814b858a5383ef5fc623d3
msgid ""
"You can also create custom dashboards and alerts to monitor the metrics "
"and logs from the connected units. See the `official documentation "
"<https://grafana.com/docs/grafana/latest/>`_ for more information on how "
"to use Grafana."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:185 f3662b5f73fd4f499bba3c085cbec92d
msgid "Prometheus metrics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:187 466f11d6d0744806a867f2d279812899
msgid ""
"Prometheus metrics are collected using Netdata and stored in a Prometheus"
" database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:189 3234360cf8bd41e8955a75598000ae24
msgid "Metrics exported for each unit includes the following labels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:191 797ae1f725554826ba94d66bb542cd43
msgid ""
"``instance`` the VPN IP of the connected machine with the Netdata port "
"(eg. ``172.19.64.3:19999``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:192 e85a3469fc2f43049b2d0d06ad587c3b
msgid "``job`` fixed to `node`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:193 2703da16a34a490183bc0d11428582fd
msgid "``node`` the VPN IP of the connected machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:194 1ac6c9e059a94cb59cc0c2b98a1eb31d
msgid "``unit`` the unit unique name of the connected machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:196 bcf1dcfb9c3245b38a26ed9279c48287
msgid "Such metrics are visible inside the ``Operating system`` dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:199 8a5adf068cf642338eeacde37d47f8aa
msgid "Timescale metrics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:201 ../../controller.rst:339
#: a5b8761da807475d9b3db6af2856aac7 de91d25f3ef149cebd9d6ecc688bd979
msgid "Subscription required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:203 beaefe2cd2fc430eb83d780fffaa7902
msgid ""
"This feature is available only if the firewall and the controller have a "
"valid subscription."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:205 5e48971404074a5abc1b01d81119b9f2
msgid ""
"The Timescale database stores the same metrics of the :ref"
":`real_time_monitoring-section` but as a timeseries saved in a PostgreSQL"
" database. Each unit sends data to the controller every 15 minutes. The "
"controller aggregates the data every 15 minutes, this means that data are"
" available inside dashboards at best with a 15 minutes delay and at worst"
" with a 30 minutes delay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:209 f1b4ad4d6def42f5b476aff988683655
msgid ""
"The controller can do extra processing on the data to provide more "
"insights. For example, the controller can geolocate the IP addresses of "
"the connected clients and of the attackers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:212 071684e9aed64a9eb3cd4ab08c07c405
msgid "These metrics are visible inside the following dashboards:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:214 b5f706e97f29468b831a39522a078765
msgid "``Network traffic``: aggregated network traffic as seen by the unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:215 efc9214e08844803ac104a7442269231
msgid ""
"``Network traffic by client``: network traffic for each client (local "
"host) connected to the unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:216 96a4ebceb51148e380c30caa62897620
msgid "``Network traffic by host``: network traffic for each remote host"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:217 03e6f09eb45342a2a6fd635ef04460de
msgid "``Security``: security events detected by the unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:218 dc8e6cb0dc9741b4bdeccacf0de28ae7
msgid ""
"``VPN``: VPN statistics for OpenVPN Road Warrior, OpenVPN tunnels and "
"IPsec tunnels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:222 f8e0eacd635c43a9bff3efa16eb84e3c
msgid ""
"Metrics retention period must be configured from the NS8 web interface "
"and is applied to both to Prometheus and Timescale databases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:230 7feb9dcdb3f343fc9375fc0609bbf0d5
msgid "Unit updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:232 4b6fa1050d404914bb36a0dddd3268b6
msgid ""
"The controller allows you to update the units directly from the "
"interface, similar to the process in :ref:`the unit web interface"
"<updates-section>`. Two types of updates are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:234 4c8bb4e7cfc24d9fb1ed608634506fa3
msgid ""
"**Package updates**: Update the packages installed on the unit. List and "
"install available updates by clicking on :guilabel:`Check packages "
"updates` in the unit menu. A modal will display the list of available "
"updates. If updates are available, apply them by clicking on the "
":guilabel:`Update` button in the modal. This is the first thing to try if"
" :ref:`version awareness<version-awareness-section>` blocks you from "
"accessing the unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:237 b66c92a35512441286ef501138b6cb00
msgid ""
"**System update**: Update the unit's system. If an image update is "
"available, a badge will appear in the unit list. Schedule an update by "
"clicking on the :guilabel:`System update` button in the unit menu. You "
"can schedule the update or update the unit immediately. This operation is"
" also available as a mass operation for multiple units under "
":guilabel:`Actions` -> :guilabel:`Update systems`. Units with a scheduled"
" image update will have a dedicated badge in the unit list. You can abort"
" the scheduled update by clicking on the :guilabel:`Cancel scheduled "
"image update` button in the unit menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:244 ea0c0c04b745499eb6d1ca962e0c7b23
msgid ""
"Please be aware that units might not send updated information when "
"undergoing upgrading process prior to unit version 1.3.0. To refresh "
"manually the information use the `guilabel`:`Sync unit info` button in "
"the unit menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:249 f4573ffbcaa946869f0e4c048399438c
msgid "SSH access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:251 7dfd4c8402f0407e9b27b142ea39ca49
msgid ""
"SSH, or Secure Shell, is a cryptographic network protocol for operating "
"network services securely over an unsecured network. SSH provides a "
"secure channel over an unsecured network in a client-server architecture,"
" connecting an SSH client application to an SSH server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:254 0bf69fac9b9c407e827c9fef8b0cf183
msgid ""
"It is possible to connect to the unit by clicking on the :guilabel:`Open "
"SSH terminal` link. The connection is made through a web-based SSH client"
" that allows access to the unit's shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:257 d9332e8f177d4660a51cdcd32101f8d2
msgid "You can connect to units using a username and password pair or an SSH key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:259 8a2b4553ab254255aea0f27f65876875
msgid ""
"Once connected, the SSH session will be started inside a new browser tab."
" Some browsers require permission to open popups for the SSH session to "
"work properly. To close the session, simply close the browser window or "
"log out from the shell using CTRL + D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:263 4556c777377b45ccbe636b587b19b2d0
msgid "Username and password"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:265 7ff4645e570b464d90ccdb066b3b4ef4
msgid ""
"The user can connect using a username and password pair of the unit in "
"the following scenarios: - The logged-in user has not generated an SSH "
"key - The public SSH key of the logged-in user hasn't been copied inside "
"the SSH authorized keys file of the unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:269 21fe6c78259a4793b63d7f3dc48810b8
msgid ""
"The user interface will display a form to enter the username and "
"password. After entering the credentials, the user can click on the "
":guilabel:`Open terminal` button to start the SSH session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:273 d5713100c910486d99377b5339810152
msgid "SSH key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:275 62038913af1e4ff6b922d3dc6a984700
msgid ""
"An SSH key pair is a set of two cryptographic keys that are used for "
"authentication when establishing a secure connection using the SSH "
"(Secure Shell) protocol. The pair consists of a private key and a public "
"key:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:278 ffcb95c32419442ba403d247cc14ba9c
msgid ""
"**Private Key**: This is kept secret and secure by the user. It should "
"never be exposed to the outside world. It is used to decrypt data that "
"has been encrypted with the public key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:280 da72d17243d34a758244647211b5092b
msgid ""
"**Public Key**: This can be freely shared and is used to encrypt data "
"that can only be decrypted with the private key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:282 474b92f646e74bd6870a4178a37231a5
msgid ""
"When you connect to a server using SSH with key pair authentication, you "
"provide your public key to the server. The server then encrypts a "
"challenge message with your public key. Your client then decrypts the "
"message with your private key and sends the result back to the server. If"
" the result is correct, the server knows that you must have the correct "
"private key and allows you to connect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:286 f5eb70e118c446d6a3574e905fa0f27e
msgid ""
"This method of authentication is more secure than using a password, as it"
" provides a form of two-factor authentication: something you have (the "
"private key file) and something you know (the passphrase to unlock the "
"private key)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:289 ddab6d582cd34e3abd7cc51bce7f7820
msgid ""
"To use an SSH key, generate a new key pair by accessing the ``Account "
"settings`` page and and clicking on the :guilabel:`Generate SSH key pair`"
" button. Enter a passphrase to protect the private key and click on the "
":guilabel:`Generate SSH key` button. The user interface will display the "
"public key, while the private key is preserved safely inside the "
"controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:293 3da07a3baa3b462694ef0bed2110ca4b
msgid ""
"Before connecting to the unit, you must copy the public key and paste it "
"into the unit's SSH authorized keys file. You can do it from the ``Unit "
"manager`` page, by clicking on the :guilabel:`Actions` button and "
"selecting :guilabel:`Send SSH public key`. Choose the units you want to "
"send the key to and click on the :guilabel:`Send SSH key` button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:297 a8484e71a6c24962a2d44d65caa7f734
msgid ""
"From now on, you can connect to the unit using the SSH key pair. The user"
" interface will display a form to enter the passphrase when clicking on "
"the :guilabel:`Open terminal` button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../controller.rst:300 45dcaec33ba74b59808d39afa6d53df7
msgid ""
